The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Videocon, GAIL in oil hunt pact

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, June 23: Videocon Industries has signed a memorandum of understanding with GAIL (India) Ltd to secure petroleum exploration and extraction blocks at home and abroad.

 Under the agreement, the companies can set up a company to operate the production blocks secured together, Videocon has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Videocon chairman V.N. Dhoot told The Telegraph, This MoU is different from the consortium that we have formed with GAIL. That was only for Oman. 

 Under this agreement, the two firms will explore global opportunities. 




